p-values are much smaller than 0.05. I would say that the residuals are fairly independent from each other, as they are more or less scattered around the value 0. However, we can see some dependency for the biggest fitted values. Residuals distribution is normal from the theoretical quantile -4 to 3. It is not normal for the outliers between 3 and 4. The residuals variation shows some increase in the extremes, but it is not much. Overall I would say we can trust the p-values, as all this conditions are fulfilled.
